=============================================================================================================
Notes:

MacOS X: 
  The provided universal binary QuantumKernelX (the MathLink executable) has been compiled on 
  32 bit - Mathematica 6 MacOS X 10.4 PowerPC G5 and
  runs on 64 and 32 bit PowerPC and 32 bit Intel archtiectures. For 64bit Intel please compile again.

Linux:
  The provided Makefiles have been tested on Ubuntu Linux (feisty) 32 bit and 64 bit.

Windows: 
  tested on Windows XP, should run on Windows 2000 and Windows Vista.
  For compiling you need to install a GNU compiler and tools, e.g., cygwin from http://www.cygwin.com , 
  including g++ and  make .
  It is recommended to install cygwin to C:\cygwin

=============================================================================================================

Building the executables on Mathematica 6 from this directory:

Run from a terminal (shell):

MacOS X univerisal binary :
make -f Makefile.macosx clean;  make -f Makefile.macosx

Linux 32 bit:
make -f Makefile.linux32 clean;  make -f Makefile.linux32

Linux 64 bit:
make -f Makefile.linux64 clean;  make -f Makefile.linux64

Windows 32 bit:
make -f Makefile.windows clean; make -f Makefile.windows

================================================================================================================
Then copy the resulting Mathlink executable, i.e., QuantumKernel, QuantumKernelX, QuantumKernel32 or QuantumKernel64
to the VQM package directory, i.e., to the parent directory of this Source directory.


